{"id": 223753222, "title": "Southampton promoted to Premier League after beating Leeds in play-off final", "text": "Armstrong scored his 24th goal of the season at Wembley (Picture: Getty) Southampton have sealed their return to the Premier League after beating Leeds United 1-0 in the Championship play-off final at Wembley. In a game worth \u00a3170million to the winners, the Saints return to the top flight of English football at the first time of asking thanks to Adam Armstrong\u2019s winner in the capital. Russell Martin\u2019s side join Leicester City and Ipswich Town in securing promotion. Southampton snatched the lead 24 minutes into the game, with Armstrong timing his run to perfection to latch onto Will Smallbone\u2019s through ball. With Leeds\u2019 defence sleeping, Armstrong expertly slotted into the far corner beyond the onrushing Illan Meslier. Leeds pushed for an equaliser in the second-half with Dan James rattling the cross bar with a superb effort from range. Alex McCarthy in the Saints goal was also forced into sone vital saves, denying James late on in injury time. More to follow", "summary": "The Saints are back in the top flight of English football.", "url": "https://metro.co.uk/2024/05/26/southampton-promoted-premier-league-beating-leeds-play-off-final-20914150/", "image": "https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/GettyImages-2154216537.jpg?quality=90&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 16:04:34", "author": "Tony Mogan", "authors": ["Tony Mogan"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.46}